&ldquo;Has anyone ever participated in a Capture-the-flag style hacking event? Does anyone fancy trying one?&rdquo;
 So, fairly innocuously, began what turned out to be a pretty interesting event.
We recently ran a Capture the Flag (CTF) event at my workplace. For anyone unfamiliar with the concept (which, in all fairness, was the position of many of the participants), there are a few variants of CTF events but the essential premise is this: teams compete to find specific, intended vulnerabilities in a software application.
